16/01/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- The General Staff announced on Tuesday (January 15th) that military jets conducted attacks against alleged bases of the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq.
In a statement on its website, the army said that the attack on Tuesday morning targeted bases of the PKK's Kongra-Gel branch.
The army stressed extreme care was taken not to strike any civilians.
Also Tuesday, Turkey's General Staff Deputy Chief General Ergin Saygun paid a surprise visit to Iraq to meet with Iraqi and US commanders.
They discussed joint anti-terrorism efforts and military co-operation.
(Zaman - 16/01/08;
CNN Turk, Anadolu news agency, RIA Novosti, DPA, Reuters, AFP - 15/01/08)
